quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,Did We not soothe your heart
  94,2,And lift from you your burden
  94,3,Which weighed down your back
  94,4,And raised for you your reputation
  94,5,With hardship comes ease
  94,6,With hardship comes ease
  94,7,"When your work is done, turn to devotion"
  94,8,And to your Lord turn for everything
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,And Mount Sinai
  95,3,And this safe land
  95,4,We created man in the best design
  95,5,Then reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,Except those who believe and do righteous deeds; for them is a reward without end
  95,7,So why do you still reject the religion
  95,8,Is God not the Wisest of the wise
  96,1,"Read: In the Name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,Created man from a clot
  96,3,"Read: And your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,He who taught by the pen
  96,5,Taught man what he never knew
  96,6,"In fact, man oversteps all bounds"
  96,7,When he considers himself exempt
  96,8,But to your Lord is the return
  96,9,Have you seen him who prevents
  96,10,A servant when he prays
  96,11,Do you think he is upon guidance
  96,12,Or advocates righteousness
  96,13,Do you see how he disbelieved and turned away
  96,14,Does he not know that God sees
  96,15,"No. If he does not desist, We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,"A deceitful, sinful forelock"
  96,17,Let him call on his gang
  96,18,We will call the Guards
  96,19,"No, do not obey him; but kneel down, and come near"
  97,1,We sent it down on the Night of Decree
  97,2,But what will convey to you what the Night of Decree is
  97,3,The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"In it descend the angels and the Spirit, by the leave of their Lord, with every command"
  97,5,Peace it is; until the rise of dawn
  98,1,"Those who disbelieved among the People of the Scripture, and the Polytheists, were not apart, until the Clear Evidence came to them"
  98,2,A messenger from God reciting purified scripts
  98,3,In them are valuable writings
  98,4,"Those who were given the Scripture did not splinter, except after the Clear Evidence came to them"
  98,5,"They were commanded only to worship God, devoting their faith to Him alone, and to practice regular prayer, and to give alms. That is the upright religion"
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve among the People of the Scripture, and the Polytheists, will be in the Fire of Hell, where they will abide forever. These are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,As for those who believe and lead a righteous life—these are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Lord: Gardens of Eternity beneath which rivers flow, where they will abide forever. God is pleased with them, and they are pleased with Him. That is for whoever fears His Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken with its quake
  99,2,And the earth brings out its loads
  99,3,"And man says, 'What is the matter with it"
  99,4,"On that Day, it will tell its tales"
  99,5,For your Lord will have inspired it
  99,6,"On that Day, the people will emerge in droves, to be shown their works"
  99,7,Whoever has done an atom's weight of good will see it
  99,8,And whoever has done an atom's weight of evil will see it
  100,1,By the racers panting
  100,2,Igniting sparks
  100,3,Raiding at dawn
  100,4,Raising clouds of dust
  100,5,Storming into the midst
  100,6,"Indeed, the human being is ungrateful to his Lord"
  100,7,And he bears witness to that
  100,8,And he is fierce in his love of wealth